com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents.sequence

Class SequenceListSummary

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents.sequence.SequenceListSummary
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    XMLSerializable, XMLSerializable.OldVersionCompatible

    public final class SequenceListSummary
extends Object
implements XMLSerializable, XMLSerializable.OldVersionCompatible
    Provides a summary of data in a list of sequences. For example it provides the distribution of sequence lengths, sequence qualities, and annotation types.

    The list returned from SequenceListDocument.getNucleotideSequences() or SequenceListDocument.getAminoAcidSequences() may optionally implement the interface SequenceListSummary.Provider to provide a summary of the information contained within it. DefaultAlignmentDocument.getSummary also provides a summary if it stores its non-reference sequences on disk instead of in memory.

    This class is not thread safe while being constructed, but once finishedAddingSequences(jebl.util.ProgressListener) has been called this class becomes immutable and thread safe. Instances of this class created using SequenceListSummary(org.jdom.Element) are thread safe since they are immutable.

    Since:
    API 4.40 (Geneious 5.4.0)

        Convert object to a JDOM element. The representation should be complete so that XMLSerializable.fromXML(org.jdom.Element) can completely restore the objects representation.

      • getSequenceLengthsExcludingGaps

        public ValueAndFrequencyDistribution getSequenceLengthsExcludingGaps()
        Gets the distribution of ungapped sequence lengths of all sequences managed by this summary. For example if a sequence is "--GATT--ACA----" then its ungapped length is 7.

        This method can not be called until finishedAddingSequences(jebl.util.ProgressListener) has been called.

        Returns:
        the distribution of ungapped sequence lengths of all sequences managed by this summary
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if finishedAddingSequences(jebl.util.ProgressListener) has not yet been called.
        See Also:
        getSequenceLengthsExcludingGapsTrimmed()

      • getSequenceLengthsExcludingGapsTrimmed

        public ValueAndFrequencyDistribution getSequenceLengthsExcludingGapsTrimmed()
        Gets the distribution of ungapped sequence lengths of all sequences managed by this summary after trim annotations have been applied. If there are no trim annotations present, the lengths are the same as those returned from getSequenceLengthsExcludingGaps(). For example if a sequence is "--GATT--ACA----" and it has a trim annotation covering the "GA" then its ungapped trimmed length is 5.

        This method can not be called until finishedAddingSequences(jebl.util.ProgressListener) has been called.

        Returns:
        the distribution of ungapped sequence lengths of all sequences managed by this summary after trim annotations have been applied.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if finishedAddingSequences(jebl.util.ProgressListener) has not yet been called.
        See Also:
        getSequenceLengthsExcludingGaps()

      • getCoverage

        public SequenceListSummary.Coverage getCoverage(int minResidueIndex,
                                       int maxResidueIndexExclusive)
        If this summary is for an alignment, gets an approximate coverage for the given range. The approximation is that for performance reasons it may return a coverage for a slightly larger range of values than those provided. For example if residues 70 through 90 are requested, the calling code may return values for the range 64 to 96.
        Parameters:
        minResidueIndex - the first 0-based index of the position to get the coverage for
        maxResidueIndexExclusive - the final 0-based index (exclusive) of the position to get the coverage for
        Returns:
        an approximation of the coverage over this range
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if this summary is not for an alignment

      • getColumnsWithGapsOverPercentage

        public BitSet getColumnsWithGapsOverPercentage(double percentage)
        If this summary is for an alignment gets a BitSet indicating which columns contain over the given percentage of gaps. This method may return null if this information is not cached with this summary. For circular alignments, the BitSet is only equal in length to circular alignment length.
        Parameters:
        percentage - the percentage
        Returns:
        a BitSet where BitSet.get(int) is true for each column that contains over the given percentage of gaps, or null if this information is unavailable.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if this summary is not for an alignment
        Since:

        public Boolean hasAnyReadsMappedToMultipleLocations()
        Returns:
        null if this summary was created prior to Geneious 6.0. True if this summary is for an alignment and there is at least 1 read in the alignment mapped to more than 1 location as defined by DocumentField.NUMBER_OF_MAPPED_LOCATIONS, false if not.

        API 4.600 (Geneious 6.0.0)
